{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust as an accountant by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, several mitigating factors are taken into account: the defendant has no prior criminal record, the motivation was to pay off personal debts rather than fund a luxurious lifestyle, and they have made a good-faith effort to partially pay back the stolen funds. Balancing the aggravating factor of the abuse of professional trust against the strong mitigating factors of restitution efforts and lack of criminal history, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate, to be followed by supervised probation and a mandatory schedule to complete the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
